parameters: Kru: "Thanks everyone for getting ready."
Villager A: "This is nothing at all!"
Villager B: "Alright! Let's do this."
Kru: "About that, I have a favor to ask of everyone..."
Villager C: "What is it?"
Kru: "I want everyone to avoid joining the fight as much as possible."
Villager A: "Eh! What do you mean by that!"

Kru: "I think this battle is going to be quite tough... Honestly, the
difference in strength is clear. I don't want any of you to die... That's
why I want you to focus on support from the rear as much as possible."
Villager D: "Kru..."

Kru: "I'll stand on the front lines and fight. And if the enemy crosses the
absolute defense line, I want you to surrender peacefully."
Villager B: "But that's...!"

Kru: "I know I'm asking for something difficult, but I want you to look at
the current situation. Women, children, and the elderly are coming to the
battlefield."

Kru: "Even if we gather everyone in the village, only a few can actually
fight. In such a situation, it's much better to surrender and live than to
die in vain. Do you understand?"
Villager C: "But then, what's the point of fighting in the first place..."

Kru: "No, that's not a problem. Not to boast, but I served as the kingdom's
swordmaster."
Villager A: "We know that."
Kru: "And the kingdom's soldiers have almost no real combat experience."
Villager B: "Eh? What do you mean by that?"

Kru: "It means that most of the rough stuff was settled by me stepping
forward, so the other soldiers didn't have to fight."
Villager D: "Eh, can such a thing really happen?"

Kru: "(No, what a terrible lie I've told... But it's true that the
kingdom's army is weak.)"

Kru: "Well, yeah. The kingdom's army is mostly made up of nobles who are
reluctant to fight. By the way, I've fought against the army of a
neighboring country by myself before."
Villager A: "You're kidding..."

Kru: "I almost died at that time, but I think I can hold out for a day or
so."
Villager B: "But to impose such a burden on Kru alone..."

Kru: "I love this village... I don't mind risking my life to save it... But
if we win this fight and I'm still alive, there's something I want to ask
of everyone."
Villager A: "What is it?"
Kru: "I want you to accept my marriage to Umi!"
Villager A: "Eh!"
Villager D: "That is..."
Kru: "Please! I want you to welcome me into this village!"
Villager B: "Kru..."
Villager C: "Don't be so formal."
Kru: "Eh?"
Villager E: "Kru is already one of our village members."

Villager D: "And we've been thinking it's just a matter of time before you
and Umi-chan get together."
Kru: "Everyone..."

Villager A: "Then after the battle is over, we'll have to celebrate in a
big way!"
Villager B: "Yeah! Let's drink until Kru passes out!"
Kru: "Hahaha! Please go easy on me."
Villager E: "Then let's definitely win this battle!"
Kru: "Yeah! Definitely!"
